select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fintparentprofilenumber, fintprofilenumber, fstraccounttype, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, fstrstatus, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp
from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
where flngaccountkey = 1003504896
order by fintprofilenumber, fintparentprofilenumber, record_effective_timestamp

select 
        case when start_parent_profile_type = ref.fstrdecode2 and ref.fstrdecode2 is not NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type is as expected (not N/A) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type = 'N/A' and ref.fstrdecode2 is NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type = N/A (fstrdecode is NULL) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type <> nvl(ref.fstrdecode2, 'N/A') then 'start_parent_profile_type is not as expected - CHECK!!'
             else '???' end chk,
        act.*, acct.fintprofilenumber, acct.fintparentprofilenumber, pp.flngcustomerkey, pp.fstrprofiletype, ref.fstrdecode2, pp.record_effective_timestamp profile_rec_eff_ts, pp.record_expiry_timestamp profile_rec_exp_ts
    from (
        select dip_account_id, account_key, account_origin, account_ird_number, account_type_code, start_profile_number, start_parent_profile_number, start_parent_profile_type, 
            record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200311
        from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200320
        where account_origin = 'START'
        and dip_account_sk > 0
        and account_key = '1003504896'
        -- and account_key = '2065829184'
        ) act
    left outer join ( --join here to get flngcustomerkey from flngaccount_key for a specific date/period (one account may belong to different customers overtime)
        select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fintparentprofilenumber, fintprofilenumber, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.app_tblaccount
        from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
        -- where flngaccountkey = 1298320512 --has 2 flngcustomerkey but they're in consecutive period
        ) acct
    on cast(act.account_key as int) = acct.flngaccountkey
    and act.record_effective_timestamp between acct.record_effective_timestamp and acct.record_expiry_timestamp
    -- left outer join test_dw.app_tblprofile pp
    left outer join test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblProfile_20200320 pp
    on pp.flngcustomerkey = acct.flngcustomerkey
    and pp.fintprofilenumber = cast(act.start_parent_profile_number as int)
    and act.record_effective_timestamp between pp.record_effective_timestamp and pp.record_expiry_timestamp
    left outer join test_dw.ref_lanprofiletype ref
    on ref.fstrprofiletype = pp.fstrprofiletype

SELECT 'old',
       CAST(CASE
                WHEN tr.treg_status = 'C' THEN IFNULL(mp_cr.dip_description, IFNULL(cr.description, 'Unknown'))
                ELSE 'N/A'
            END AS VARCHAR(30)) AS cessation_reason,
       CAST(CASE
                WHEN tr.treg_status = 'C' THEN IFNULL(mp_cr.dip_code_value, IFNULL(tr.cessation_reason_code, 'Unknown'))
                ELSE 'N/A'
            END AS VARCHAR(10)) AS cessation_reason_code
FROM test_refined.rfn_ae_timeline_f AS timeline
LEFT JOIN
     test_refined.rfn_account_sk_map AS sk_map 
ON   timeline.ird_no = sk_map.ird_no
AND  timeline.edw_tax_type = sk_map.edw_tax_type
AND  timeline.edw_location_number = sk_map.edw_location_number
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp = sk_map.record_effective_timestamp
LEFT JOIN 
     test_refined.crw_ae_tax_registrations AS tr 
ON   timeline.ird_no = tr.ird_number
AND  timeline.edw_location_number = tr.location_number
AND  timeline.edw_tax_type = tr.tax_type
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp BETWEEN tr.record_effective_timestamp AND tr.record_expiry_timestamp
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp >= tr.treg_date_start
AND  tr.tax_type NOT IN ('PAY',
                        'PIE',
                        'INC',
                        'GST')
LEFT JOIN
     test_refined.mp_source_code mp_cr 
ON   tr.cessation_reason_code = mp_cr.source_code_value
--AND  (tr.tax_type = mp_cr.source_tax_type OR mp_cr.source_tax_type = '')
 AND  tr.tax_type                        IN ('', mp_cr.source_tax_type)
--AND  tr.tax_type = IF(mp_cr.source_tax_type = '', tr.tax_type, mp_cr.source_tax_type) 
AND  mp_cr.source_system = 'FIRST'
AND  mp_cr.source_code_name = 'CESSATION_REASON'
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp BETWEEN mp_cr.record_effective_timestamp AND mp_cr.record_expiry_timestamp
LEFT JOIN 
     test_refined.crw_ae_tax_cessation_reasons AS cr 
ON   cr.cessation_reason_code = tr.cessation_reason_code
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp BETWEEN cr.record_effective_timestamp AND cr.record_expiry_timestamp
WHERE tr.ird_number = 63742044
AND  tr.tax_type = 'PPL'
UNION ALL
SELECT 'new',
   CAST(CASE
                WHEN tr.treg_status = 'C' THEN IFNULL(mp_cr.dip_description, IFNULL(cr.description, 'Unknown'))
                ELSE 'N/A'
            END AS VARCHAR(30)) AS cessation_reason,
       CAST(CASE
                WHEN tr.treg_status = 'C' THEN IFNULL(mp_cr.dip_code_value, IFNULL(tr.cessation_reason_code, 'Unknown'))
                ELSE 'N/A'
            END AS VARCHAR(10)) AS cessation_reason_code
FROM test_refined.rfn_ae_timeline_f AS timeline
LEFT JOIN
     test_refined.rfn_account_sk_map AS sk_map 
ON   timeline.ird_no = sk_map.ird_no
AND  timeline.edw_tax_type = sk_map.edw_tax_type
AND  timeline.edw_location_number = sk_map.edw_location_number
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp = sk_map.record_effective_timestamp
LEFT JOIN 
     test_refined.crw_ae_tax_registrations AS tr 
ON   timeline.ird_no = tr.ird_number
AND  timeline.edw_location_number = tr.location_number
AND  timeline.edw_tax_type = tr.tax_type
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp BETWEEN tr.record_effective_timestamp AND tr.record_expiry_timestamp
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp >= tr.treg_date_start
AND  tr.tax_type NOT IN ('PAY',
                        'PIE',
                        'INC',
                        'GST')
LEFT JOIN
     test_refined.mp_source_code mp_cr 
ON   tr.cessation_reason_code = mp_cr.source_code_value
--AND  (tr.tax_type = mp_cr.source_tax_type OR mp_cr.source_tax_type = '')
--AND  tr.tax_type                        IN ('', mp_cr.source_tax_type)
AND  mp_cr.source_tax_type IN ('', tr.tax_type)
AND  mp_cr.source_system = 'FIRST'
AND  mp_cr.source_code_name = 'CESSATION_REASON'
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp BETWEEN mp_cr.record_effective_timestamp AND mp_cr.record_expiry_timestamp
LEFT JOIN 
     test_refined.crw_ae_tax_cessation_reasons AS cr 
ON   cr.cessation_reason_code = tr.cessation_reason_code
AND  timeline.record_effective_timestamp BETWEEN cr.record_effective_timestamp AND cr.record_expiry_timestamp
WHERE tr.ird_number = 63742044
AND  tr.tax_type = 'PPL'

CREATE VIEW dev_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_studylinkmaintainlg
AS SELECT 
z.fi64MaintainLogKey,
z.flngAccountKey,
z.fstrCorrelationID,
z.fstrIRDNumber,
z.fstrFamilyName,
z.fstrFirstName,
z.fstrMiddleName,
z.fdtmDOB,
z.fstrAccountType,
z.fstrAddressLine1,
z.fstrAddressLine2,
z.fstrSuburb,
z.fstrCity,
z.fstrPostCode,
z.fstrAddressAction,
z.fblnAddressProcessed,
z.fstrPhoneHome,
z.fstrPhoneHomeAction,
z.fblnPhoneHomeProcessed,
z.fstrPhoneWork,
z.fstrPhoneWorkAction,
z.fblnPhoneWorkProcessed,
z.fstrPhoneMobile,
z.fstrPhoneMobileAction,
z.fblnPhoneMobileProcessed,
z.fstrEmail,
z.fstrEmailAction,
z.fblnEmailProcessed,
z.fdtmReceived,
z.fdtmProcessed,
z.fstrWho,
z.fdtmWhen,
z.record_effective_timestamp,
z.record_expiry_timestamp,
z.record_active_flag, 
z.record_deleted_flag,
z.insert_object_run_key,
z.update_object_run_key
 FROM DEV_RAW.app_tblnz_studylinkmaintainlg z
left join 
DEV_RAW.app_tblaccount ac
ON z.flngAccountKey = ac.flngAccountKey
left join 
DEV_RAW.app_tblcustomerinfo cl 
ON ac.flngcustomerkey = cl.flngcustomerkey
WHERE
nvl(ac.record_active_flag, 'Y') = 'Y'
AND nvl(ac.record_deleted_flag, 'N') = 'N'
AND nvl(cl.fstrcustomerlevel, 'STD') = 'STD'
AND nvl(cl.record_active_flag, 'Y') = 'Y'
AND nvl(cl.record_deleted_flag, 'N') = 'N'

Select a.fstrid,a.flngcustomerkey, b.steve_ird from

(SELECT
                    s1.fstrid,
                    s1.flngcustomerkey
                FROM
                    prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo s1
                WHERE
                    s1.record_active_flag = 'Y'
                    AND s1.record_deleted_flag = 'N')a
                    
                    join (select cast(ird_number as string) as steve_ird from lab_cora_team.steverees2 ) b
on a.fstrid=b.steve_ird
select count(customer_key),type from zz_train_r3a_customer_interactions group by type

select date_trunc('day', record_effective_timestamp) AS return_effective_day
     , date_trunc('month', fdtmwhen) as Rec_Month
     , count(*) as Recs
from prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblperiodbillitem
group by date_trunc('day', record_effective_timestamp), date_trunc('month', fdtmwhen)
order by date_trunc('day', record_effective_timestamp), date_trunc('month', fdtmwhen)

SELECT * FROM prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim
where customer_key ='100044928'
and record_active_flag ='Y'
LIMIT 10

SELECT fstrwho,fdtmwhen,fstrcrmsource,fstrcrmtype,flngcustomerkey,fstrsourcetype,fstrdata
FROM prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcrmextendedlog 
-- where flngcustomerkey = 847342848
-- and fstrcrmtype = 'Fast.Customer.Note'
where
 fdtmwhen > '2019-12-05'

and (upper(fstrdata) like "%CORONAVIRUS%" or upper(fstrdata) like "%CORONA VIRUS%"
or upper(fstrdata) like "%COVID19%" or upper(fstrdata) like "%COVID 19%" or upper(fstrdata) like "%COVID-19%" )
and fstrsourcetype ='FOH'
order by fdtmwhen DESC
-- and fstrwho = '90axw1'

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, c.fstrZIP as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = i.record_active_flag
where a.party_type = 'Individual' and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC') or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))

group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, c.fstrZIP, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

with tableA1 as
(
  select a2.ird_number, max(a2.date_due) as date_due
 from
 (
    select a1.ird_number, a1.date_due, a1.date_applied,
      max(a1.date_applied) over (partition by a1.ird_number) as max_date_applied
    from
    (
      select ird_number, date_due, from_timestamp(date_due, "dd/MM") as daymonth_date_due,
        date_applied
      from lab_fcp_raw_restricted_access.dss_transaction_due_dates
      where return_period_date = "2019-03-31"
        and date_applied <= "2020-02-08"
        and (date_ceased is null or date_ceased > "2020-02-08") 
        and tax_type in ("INC", "FAM", "SLS")
        and transaction_code in ("1300", "1320", "1110")  -- 1300 = terminal assessment, 1110 = SLS interim repayment, 1320 = SLS assessment 
    ) a1 
    where a1.daymonth_date_due in ("07/02", "07/04")
  ) a2
  where a2.date_applied = a2.max_date_applied
  group by a2.ird_number
)
select * from tableA1 limit 10

select 
        case when start_parent_profile_type = ref.fstrdecode2 and ref.fstrdecode2 is not NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type is as expected (not N/A) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type = 'N/A' and ref.fstrdecode2 is NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type = N/A (fstrdecode is NULL) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type <> nvl(ref.fstrdecode2, 'N/A') then 'start_parent_profile_type is not as expected - CHECK!!'
             else '???' end chk,
        act.*, acct.fintprofilenumber, acct.fintparentprofilenumber, pp.flngcustomerkey, pp.fstrprofiletype, ref.fstrdecode2, pp.record_effective_timestamp profile_rec_eff_ts, pp.record_expiry_timestamp profile_rec_exp_ts
    from (
        select dip_account_id, account_key, account_origin, account_ird_number, account_type_code, start_profile_number, start_parent_profile_number, start_parent_profile_type, 
            record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200311
        from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200320
        where account_origin = 'START'
        and dip_account_sk > 0
        -- and account_key = '1003504896'
        and account_key = '2065829184'
        ) act
    left outer join ( --join here to get flngcustomerkey from flngaccount_key for a specific date/period (one account may belong to different customers overtime)
        select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fintparentprofilenumber, fintprofilenumber, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.app_tblaccount
        from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
        -- where flngaccountkey = 1298320512 --has 2 flngcustomerkey but they're in consecutive period
        ) acct
    on cast(act.account_key as int) = acct.flngaccountkey
    and act.record_effective_timestamp between acct.record_effective_timestamp and acct.record_expiry_timestamp
    -- left outer join test_dw.app_tblprofile pp
    left outer join test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblProfile_20200320 pp
    on pp.flngcustomerkey = acct.flngcustomerkey
    and pp.fintprofilenumber = cast(act.start_parent_profile_number as int)
    and act.record_effective_timestamp between pp.record_effective_timestamp and pp.record_expiry_timestamp
    left outer join test_dw.ref_lanprofiletype ref
    on ref.fstrprofiletype = pp.fstrprofiletype

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, c.fstrZIP as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = i.record_active_flag
where a.party_type = 'Individual' and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC') or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))

group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, c.fstrZIP, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, c.fstrZIP as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = i.record_active_flag
where a.party_type = 'Individual' and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC') or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))

group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, c.fstrZIP, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_keypoints_IR9 as
with tableA as
(
  select a1.*
  from
  (
    select a.flngcustomerkey, a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod,
      0 as salWage, 
(nvl(ir.fcurEXEMPTMAORIAUTHORITY, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurOTHERMAORIAUTHORITY, 0)) * 1 as related, 
(nvl(ir.fcurOTHERDIVIDENDS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurOTHERINTEREST, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurEXEMPTDIVIDENDS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurEXEMPTINTEREST, 0)) * 1 as divInt, 
(nvl(ir.fcurOTHEROTHERINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurEXEMPTOTHERINCOME, 0)) * 1 as business, 
0 as salWageCredits, 
0 as relatedCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurIMPUTATIONCREDITS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurRWT, 0)) * 1 as divIntCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurOVERSEASTAX, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurOTHERTAXCREDITS, 0)) * 1 as businessCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurRESIDUALINCOMETAX, 0)) * 1 as RIT,
      ir.fdtmwhen,
--      ir.record_effective_timestamp,
--      max(ir.record_effective_timestamp) over (partition by a.flngcustomerkey,
--           a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod) as max_keypoint_timestamp
      max(ir.fdtmwhen) over (partition by a.flngcustomerkey,
           a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod) as max_keypoint_timestamp
     

    from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_return a
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tbldocsetdoc b
      on a.fi64docsetkey = b.fi64docsetkey
      and b.fdtmreversed > now()   -- to ensure the record is not reversed
      and b.record_effective_timestamp <= "2020-02-08"
      and (b.record_expiry_timestamp > "2020-02-08" or
             b.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
    join lab_daur_project.app_tblnz_rtnnitclb ir
      on b.flngdockey = ir.flngdockey
        and ir.fdtmwhen <= "2020-02-08"
--      and ir.record_effective_timestamp <= "2020-02-08"
--      and (ir.record_expiry_timestamp > "2020-02-08" or
--             ir.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
  ) a1
--  where a1.record_effective_timestamp = max_keypoint_timestamp
  where a1.fdtmwhen = a1.max_keypoint_timestamp 
)
select a.flngcustomerkey, a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod,
  salWage, related, divInt, business, salWageCredits, relatedCredits, divIntCredits, businessCredits, RIT
from tableA a

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_keypoints_ind as
with tableA as
(
  select a.flngcustomerkey, a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod,
    fdtmdue,
    (nvl(ir.fcurTOTALGROSSINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALGROSSSCHEDULARPAYMENT, 0)) * 1 as salWage, 
(nvl(ir.fcurTOTALACTIVELTCINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALESTATEORTRUSTEEINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurSHAREHOLDEREMPLOYEESALARY, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALACTIVEPTSHPINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALMAORIDISTRIBUTIONS, 0)) * 1 as related, 
(nvl(ir.fcurTOTALGROSSDIVIDENDS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALGROSSINTEREST, 0)) * 1 as divInt, 
(nvl(ir.fcurSELFEMPLOYEDNETINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurNETRENTS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALOTHERNETINCOME, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALOVERSEASINCOME, 0)) * 1 as business, 
(nvl(ir.fcurTOTALINCOMEWITHTAXDEDUCTED, 0)) * 1 as salWageCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurTOTALLTCTAXCREDITS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALTAXPAIDBYTRUSTEES, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALPARTNERSHIPTAXCREDITS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALMAORICREDITS, 0)) * 1 as relatedCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurTOTALIMPUTATIONCREDITS, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALDIVIDENDRWT, 0) + nvl(ir.fcurTOTALRWT, 0)) * 1 as divIntCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurTOTALOVERSEASTAXPAID, 0)) * 1 as businessCredits, 
(nvl(ir.fcurRESIDUALINCOMETAX, 0)) * 1 as RIT,
    ir.record_effective_timestamp,
    max(ir.record_effective_timestamp) over (partition by a.flngcustomerkey,
         a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod) as max_keypoint_timestamp
  from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_return a
  join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tbldocsetdoc b
    on a.fi64docsetkey = b.fi64docsetkey
    and b.fdtmreversed > now()   -- to ensure the record is not reversed
    and b.record_effective_timestamp <= "2020-02-08"
    and (b.record_expiry_timestamp > "2020-02-08" or
           b.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
  join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_rtniit ir
    on b.flngdockey = ir.flngdockey
    and ir.record_effective_timestamp <= "2020-02-08"
    and (ir.record_expiry_timestamp > "2020-02-08" or
           ir.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
)
select * 
from tableA
where record_effective_timestamp = max_keypoint_timestamp

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_writeOff as
-- get customerkey for FIRST data
with tableA as
(
  select b.flngcustomerkey, a.ird_number, a.return_period_date, 
    a.write_off_inc, a.write_off_fam, a.write_off_sls
  from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_writeOff_FIRST a
  join lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_base b
    on a.ird_number = b.ird_number
),
--check whether customers are subjected to write off in START
-- only consider START info when it happens after its release
tableC1 as
(
  select a1.*
  from
  (
    select distinct b.flngcustomerkey, b.flngaccountkey, b.fstraccounttype,
      b.ird_number, b.tax_type, b.fdtmfilingperiod,
      a.flngtranskey,     --- this is the transaction key
      case when b.tax_type in ("FAM", "INC") and a.fdtmwhen > "2019-04-20" then 1
           when b.tax_type = "SLS" and a.fdtmwhen > "2020-04-20" then 1
      else 0 end as wanted_records
    from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_base_elements b
    join lab_daur_project.app_tbltransaction a
      on a.flngaccountkey = b.flngaccountkey
      and a.fdtmfilingperiod = b.fdtmfilingperiod
      and a.fstrtranstype = "WOOTC"  -- financial hardship write off code
      and a.fdtmwhen <= add_months("2020-02-07", 3)  -- limit the write off to before the end date.
  ) a1
  where a1.wanted_records = 1
),
-- The writeoff may be reversed, so we need to get the transaction key to
-- check whether there is any reverse after the writeoff date.

tableC2 as
(
  select distinct c1.flngcustomerkey, c1.flngaccountkey, c1.fstraccounttype,
    c1.ird_number, c1.tax_type, c1.fdtmfilingperiod
  from tableC1 c1
  left join lab_daur_project.app_tbltransaction b
  on c1.flngaccountkey = b.flngaccountkey
    and c1.fdtmfilingperiod = b.fdtmfilingperiod
    and c1.flngtranskey = b.flnglinktrans
  where b.flngaccountkey is null     -- eliminate records that have been reversed
),
--change it to wide format
tableC as
(
  select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, fdtmfilingperiod,
    max(case when tax_type = "INC" then 1 else 0 end) as WRITE_OFF_INC,
    max(case when tax_type = "FAM" then 1 else 0 end) as WRITE_OFF_FAM,
    max(case when tax_type = "SLS" then 1 else 0 end) as WRITE_OFF_SLS
  from tableC2
  group by flngcustomerkey, ird_number, fdtmfilingperiod
)
select 
  nvl(c.ird_number, a.ird_number) as ird_number,
  nvl(c.flngcustomerkey, a.flngcustomerkey) as flngcustomerkey,
  nvl(c.fdtmfilingperiod, a.return_period_date) as fdtmfilingperiod,
  nvl(c.write_off_inc, a.write_off_inc) as write_off_inc,
  nvl(c.write_off_fam, a.write_off_fam) as write_off_fam,
  nvl(c.write_off_sls, a.write_off_sls) as write_off_sls
from tableC c
full outer join tableA a
  on c.flngcustomerkey = a.flngcustomerkey
  and c.fdtmfilingperiod = a.return_period_date

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_writeOff_FIRST as

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_selfCorrect_pastYears as
--get past periods that have a balance > 0
With tableA as
(
  select a1.flngcustomerkey, a1.ird_number, a1.return_period_date,
    a1.bal_start,
    case when a1.bal_end <= 0 then 1 else 0 end as debtCleared
  from
  (
    select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date,
      sum(bal_start) as bal_start,
      sum(bal_end) as bal_end
    from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_combined_balance_past
    group by flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date
  ) a1 where a1.bal_start > 0
),
-- left join information together
tableB as
(
  select a.flngcustomerkey, a.ird_number, a.return_period_date,
    a.debtCleared,
    nvl(b.write_off, 0) as write_off,
    nvl(c.arrangement, 0) as arrangement
  from tableA a
  left join lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_writeoff_past b
    on a.flngcustomerkey = b.flngcustomerkey
    and a.ird_number = b.ird_number
    and a.return_period_date = b.return_period_date
  left join lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_Arr_past c
    on a.flngcustomerkey = c.flngcustomerkey
    and a.ird_number= c.ird_number
    and a.return_period_date = c.fdtmfilingperiod
),
tableC as
(
-- we form past self correction indicator
select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date,
  case when debtCleared = 1 and write_off = 0 then 1
       when debtCleared = 1 and write_off = 1 then 0
       when debtCleared = 0 and arrangement = 1 then 1
       when debtCleared = 0 and arrangement = 0 then 0
       else 0 end as selfCorrection
from tableB 
)
-- turn self correction information into wide format
select a.ird_number, a.flngcustomerkey, a.fdtmfilingperiod,
  nvl(b1.selfCorrection, -1) as selfCorrect_b1,
  nvl(b2.selfCorrection, -1) as selfCorrect_b2,
  nvl(b3.selfCorrection, -1) as selfCorrect_b3,
  nvl(c1.arrangement, -1) as arrangement_b1,
  nvl(c2.arrangement, -1) as arrangement_b2,
  nvl(c3.arrangement, -1) as arrangement_b3
from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_base a
left join tableC b1
  on a.flngcustomerkey = b1.flngcustomerkey
  and a.ird_number = b1.ird_number
  and b1.return_period_date = add_months(a.fdtmfilingperiod, -12 * 1)
left join tableC b2
  on a.flngcustomerkey = b2.flngcustomerkey
  and a.ird_number = b2.ird_number
  and b2.return_period_date = add_months(a.fdtmfilingperiod, -12 * 2)
left join tableC b3
  on a.flngcustomerkey = b3.flngcustomerkey
  and a.ird_number = b3.ird_number
  and b3.return_period_date = add_months(a.fdtmfilingperiod, -12 * 3)
left join lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_Arr_past c1
  on a.flngcustomerkey = c1.flngcustomerkey
  and a.ird_number = c1.ird_number
  and c1.fdtmfilingperiod = add_months(a.fdtmfilingperiod, -12 * 1)
left join lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_Arr_past c2
  on a.flngcustomerkey = c2.flngcustomerkey
  and a.ird_number = c2.ird_number
  and c2.fdtmfilingperiod = add_months(a.fdtmfilingperiod, -12 * 2)
left join lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_Arr_past c3
  on a.flngcustomerkey = c3.flngcustomerkey
  and a.ird_number = c3.ird_number
  and c3.fdtmfilingperiod = add_months(a.fdtmfilingperiod, -12 * 3)

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_Arr_past as
--table Bs is to check whether the arrangement in FIRST is adhere to 
with tableB1 as
(
  select a.*
  from
  (
    select a.flngcustomerkey, a.flngaccountkey,
       a.ird_number, b.location_number, a.return_period_date, b.tax_type, a.date_due,
       b.case_key, b.case_number,  b.case_type_code,
      b.date_start, b.date_end,
      --select the latest arrangement per tax type
      row_number() over (partition by a.ird_number, b.location_number, b.return_period_date,
        b.tax_type order by b.date_applied desc) as rn1
    from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_combined_balance_past a
    join lab_daur_project.dss_instalment_agmt_elements b
      on a.ird_number = b.ird_number
      and a.return_period_date = b.return_period_date
      and a.tax_type = b.tax_type
      --point in time
      and b.date_applied <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and (b.date_ceased is null or b.date_ceased > add_months(a.date_due, 3))
      --fence arrangement to limit it to terminal tax?
      and b.date_start > add_months(a.date_due, -6)  --6 months before due date
      -- to ensure the arrangement is still active. The other status is "S" = Settled.
      -- settled can mean the arrangement is not active? or arrangement is finalised. In the 
      -- case of full payment made, it should have been reflected in balance end date. 
      and b.arrangement_element_status = "A"
  ) a where rn1 = 1
)
,
--check arrangement details, whether customers kept up with payments
tableB2 as
(
  select a.flngcustomerkey, a.flngaccountkey,
    a.ird_number, a.location_number, a.return_period_date, a.tax_type, a.date_due,
    a.case_key, a.case_number,  a.case_type_code, a.date_start, a.date_end,
    b.total_amount, b.actual_arrangement_payment_amt, b.expected_payment_amount,
    case when b.total_amount < 1000 then 0.3 * b.total_amount
         when b.total_amount > 10000 then 0.05 * b.total_amount
         else 0.10 * b.total_amount end as allowable_var,
    b.actual_arrangement_payment_amt - b.expected_payment_amount as pay_diff
  from tableB1 a
  join lab_daur_project.dss_instalment_src_plans_sum b
    on a.ird_number = b.ird_number
    and a.location_number = b.location_number
    and a.case_key= b.case_key
    and a.case_number = b.case_number
    and a.case_type_code = b.case_type_code
    and b.date_applied <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
    and (b.date_ceased is null or b.date_ceased > add_months(a.date_due, 3))
)
,
--determining whether the arrangement is in place
tableB3 as
(
  select a.flngcustomerkey, a.flngaccountkey,
    a.ird_number, a.return_period_date, a.tax_type, a.date_due,
    a.case_key, a.case_number,  a.case_type_code, a.date_start, a.date_end,
    case when a.expected_payment_amount = 0 then 1
      when pay_diff >= 0 then 1
      when pay_diff < 0 and abs(pay_diff) < allowable_var then 1
      else 0 end as arrangement
  from tableB2 a
),
--we need to consider s400 cases, i.e. deduction notice not counted as arrangement
tableB4 as
(
  select b4.*
  from
  (
    select a.flngcustomerkey, a.flngaccountkey,
      a.ird_number, a.location_number, a.return_period_date, a.tax_type, a.date_due,
      a.case_key, a.case_number, a.case_type_code, 
      b.sequence_number, b.case_action_type_code, b.`timestamp`,
      max(b.sequence_number) over (partition by a.ird_number, a.return_period_date, a.case_number, a.location_number) as max_sequence,
      max(a.case_number) over (partition by a.ird_number, a.return_period_date, a.location_number) as max_case_number
    from tableB1 a
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.dss_case_actions b
      on a.ird_number = b.ird_number
      and a.case_type_code = b.case_type_code
      and a.case_number = b.case_number
      and a.location_number = b.location_number
      -- set a time window to inspect the action codes, i.e. after the start date of the element and point in time
        and b.`timestamp` between a.date_start and add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and b.sequence_number <> 999                        -- 999 being next action code
  ) b4 
  where sequence_number = max_sequence
    and case_number = max_case_number
),
-- form a decision to consider the FIRST arrangement is in place
tableB5 as
(
  select b3.flngcustomerkey, b3.flngaccountkey, 
    b3.ird_number, b3.return_period_date, b3.tax_type, b3.date_due,
    case when b3.arrangement = 1 and b4.case_action_type_code = "S400" then 0
      else b3.arrangement end as arrangement
  from tableB3 b3
  left join tableb4 b4
    on b3.ird_number = b4.ird_number
    and b3.return_period_date = b4.return_period_date
    and b3.case_type_code = b4.case_type_code
    and b3.case_number = b4.case_number
),
-- table C is to check arrangements in START
--get bill items, join to collection, join to payment plan
-- but we only use this table if the record is created after R3, i.e. April 20.
-- only status of 
tableC as
(

  select a1.flngcustomerkey, a1.flngaccountkey,
    a1.ird_number, a1.return_period_date, a1.tax_type, a1.date_due,
    case when a1.fblnactive = 0 then 0 
      else decode(a1.fstrstatus, "ACT", 1,
                              "PNDAPP", 1,
                              "STRKE1", 1,
                              "STRKE2", 1,
                              "STRKE3", 1,
                               0) end as arrangement
  from
  (
    select a.*,
      arr.flngcollectkey, arr.fstrstatus, arr.fblnactive, arr.record_effective_timestamp, arr.record_expiry_timestamp,
      max(arr.record_effective_timestamp) over (partition by a.ird_number, a.flngaccountkey) as max_arr_timestamp,
      -- create a feature to consider only records after releases, i.e. release 3 and release 4
      case when a.tax_type in ("INC", "FAM") and arr.record_effective_timestamp > "2019-04-20" then 1
           when a.tax_type in ("SLS") and arr.record_effective_timestamp > "2020-04-20" then 1
        else 0 end as wanted_records
    from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_combined_balance_past a
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblperiodbillitem b
      on a.flngaccountkey = b.flngaccountkey
      and b.fstrbilltype in ("STNDR2", "INCOME")
      and b.fdtmfilingperiod = a.return_period_date
      and b.fdtmdue = a.date_due
      and record_effective_timestamp <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and (record_expiry_timestamp > add_months(a.date_due, 3) or
            record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcollect coll
      on coll.flngcollectkey = b.flngCOLLECTKEY        --bill_item has been added to a collection
      and coll.record_effective_timestamp <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and (coll.record_expiry_timestamp > add_months(a.date_due, 3) or
            coll.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcollectpaymentplan arr
      on coll.flngcollectkey = arr.flngcollectkey         --collection has an arrangment associated with it
      and arr.record_effective_timestamp <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and (arr.record_expiry_timestamp > add_months(a.date_due, 3) or
            arr.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
      and arr.fdtmcreated <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and arr.fdtmcreated > add_months(a.date_due, -6)
  ) a1
  where a1.record_effective_timestamp = a1.max_arr_timestamp
    and a1.wanted_records = 1
),
--now full outer join the data from FIRST and START. Consider START data
-- if there is data in START
tableD as
(
select
  nvl(c.flngcustomerkey, b.flngcustomerkey) flngcustomerkey,
  nvl(c.flngaccountkey, b.flngaccountkey) flngaccountkey,
  nvl(c.ird_number, b.ird_number) ird_number,
  nvl(c.return_period_date, b.return_period_date) fdtmfilingperiod,
  nvl(c.tax_type, b.tax_type) tax_type,
  nvl(c.arrangement, b.arrangement) arrangement
from tableC c
full outer join tableB5 b 
  on c.flngcustomerkey = b.flngcustomerkey
    and c.flngaccountkey = b.flngaccountkey
    and c.return_period_date = b.return_period_date
)
--aggregate to customer level
select  flngcustomerkey, ird_number, fdtmfilingperiod,
  case when sum(arrangement)/count(arrangement) >= 0.5 then 1
  else 0 end as arrangement
from tableD
group by flngcustomerkey, ird_number, fdtmfilingperiod

with tableA1 as

  select flngcustomerkey, flngaccountkey, fstraccounttype, fstrfiling
  from prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblaccount
  where fstraccounttype in ("IIT", "ITN", "FAM", "SLS")
    and record_effective_timestamp <= "2020-02-08"
    and (record_expiry_timestamp > "2020-02-08" or
          record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
--    and fstrstatus = "ACT"  
),
--get account key and customerkey for first data
tableB1 as
(
  select c.flngcustomerkey, c.flngaccountkey, c.fstraccounttype,
    a.ird_number, a.tax_type, a.return_period_date, a.date_due,
    a.balance_start, a.balance_end
  from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_balances_past a
  --get customer key
  join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo b
    on a.ird_number = cast(b.fstrid as INT)
    and b.record_active_flag = "Y"
  --get account key
  join tableA1 c
    on b.flngcustomerkey = c.flngcustomerkey 
    and a.tax_type = decode(c.fstraccounttype, "IIT", "INC",
                                               "ITN", "INC",
                                               "FAM", "FAM",
                                               "SLS", "SLS",
                                               "OTH")
),
--repeat the same for writeoff identified from FIRST to get customerkey
tableB2 as
(
  select b.flngcustomerkey, 
    a.ird_number, a.return_period_date, a.write_off
  from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_writeoff_past a
  --get customer key
  join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo b
    on a.ird_number = cast(b.fstrid as INT)
    and b.record_active_flag = "Y"
),

--check whether customers are subjected to write off in START
-- only consider START info when it happens after its release
tableC1 as
(
  select a1.*
  from
  (
    select distinct b.flngcustomerkey, b.flngaccountkey, b.fstraccounttype,
      b.ird_number, b.tax_type, b.return_period_date,
      a.flngtranskey,     --- this is the transaction key
      case when b.tax_type in ("FAM", "INC") and a.fdtmwhen > "2019-04-20" then 1
           when b.tax_type = "SLS" and a.fdtmwhen > "2020-04-20" then 1
      else 0 end as wanted_records
    from tableB1 b
    join lab_daur_project.app_tbltransaction a
      on a.flngaccountkey = b.flngaccountkey
      and a.fdtmfilingperiod = b.return_period_date
      and a.fstrtranstype = "WOOTC"  -- financial hardship write off code
      and a.fdtmwhen <= add_months(b.date_due, 3)  -- limit the write off to before the end date.
  ) a1
  where a1.wanted_records = 1
),
-- The writeoff may be reversed, so we need to get the transaction key to
-- check whether there is any reverse after the writeoff date.

tableC2 as
(
  select distinct c1.flngcustomerkey, c1.flngaccountkey, c1.fstraccounttype,
    c1.ird_number, c1.tax_type, c1.return_period_date
  from tableC1 c1
  left join lab_daur_project.app_tbltransaction b
  on c1.flngaccountkey = b.flngaccountkey
    and c1.return_period_date = b.fdtmfilingperiod
    and c1.flngtranskey = b.flnglinktrans
  where b.flngaccountkey is null     -- eliminate records that have been reversed
)

--now union the FIRST and START data together
select distinct a1.* 
from
(
  select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date, write_off 
  from tableB2

  union

  select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date, 1 as write_off
  from tableC2
) a1

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, '' as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = i.record_active_flag
where a.party_type = 'Individual' and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC') or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))

group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

SELECT NDV(flngcustomerkey) AS flngcustomerkey, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(flngaccountkey) AS flngaccountkey, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(ird_number) AS ird_number, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(return_period_date) AS return_period_date, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(tax_type) AS tax_type, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), MAX(length(tax_type)), AVG(length(tax_type)), NDV(date_due) AS date_due, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(bal_start) AS bal_start, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(bal_end) AS bal_end, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE) FROM LAB_DAUR_PROJECT.WXT_SC07FEB_3_PIT0208_SCORE_COMBINED_BALANCE_PAST

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_score_combined_balance_past as
with tableA1 as
(
  select flngcustomerkey, flngaccountkey, fstraccounttype, fstrfiling
  from prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblaccount
  where fstraccounttype in ("IIT", "ITN", "FAM", "SLS")
    and record_effective_timestamp <= "2020-02-08"
    and (record_expiry_timestamp > "2020-02-08" or
          record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
    and fdtmcease > "2020-02-08"
--    and fstrstatus = "ACT"  
),
--get account key and customerkey for first data
tableC as
(
  select c.flngcustomerkey, c.flngaccountkey, c.fstraccounttype,
    a.ird_number, a.tax_type, a.return_period_date, a.date_due,
    a.balance_start, a.balance_end
  from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_training_balances_past a
  --get customer key
  join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo b
    on a.ird_number = cast(b.fstrid as INT)
    and b.record_active_flag = "Y"
  --get account key
  join tableA1 c
    on b.flngcustomerkey = c.flngcustomerkey 
    and a.tax_type = decode(c.fstraccounttype, "IIT", "INC",
                                               "ITN", "INC",
                                               "FAM", "FAM",
                                               "SLS", "SLS",
                                               "OTH")
),
--open balance for past periods in START, i.e. one day after due date
tableD1 as
(
  select a1.*
  from
  (
    select a.ird_number, a.flngcustomerkey, a.flngaccountkey, 
      a.tax_type, a.return_period_date, a.date_due,
      c.fcurbalance as bal_start,
      c.record_effective_timestamp,

      -- add a logic to only take records updated after R3 and R4
      case when a.tax_type in ("INC", "FAM") and c.record_effective_timestamp > "2019-04-20" then 1
           when a.tax_type = "SLS" and c.record_effective_timestamp > "2020-04-20" then 1
        else 0 end as wanted_records 
    from tableC a
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblperiod c
      on a.flngaccountkey = c.flngaccountkey
      and a.return_period_date = c.fdtmfilingperiod
      and c.record_effective_timestamp <= adddate(a.date_due, 1) -- add one day
      and (c.record_expiry_timestamp > adddate(a.date_due, 1) or
        c.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
  ) a1
  where a1.wanted_records = 1
),
--closing balance in START
tableD2 as
(
  select a1.*
  from
  (
    select a.ird_number, a.flngcustomerkey, a.flngaccountkey, 
      a.tax_type, a.return_period_date, a.date_due,
      c.fcurbalance as bal_end,
      c.record_effective_timestamp,

      -- add a logic to only take records updated after R3 and R4
      case when a.tax_type in ("INC", "FAM") and c.record_effective_timestamp > "2019-04-20" then 1
           when a.tax_type = "SLS" and c.record_effective_timestamp > "2020-04-20" then 1
        else 0 end as wanted_records 
    from tableC a
    join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblperiod c
      on a.flngaccountkey = c.flngaccountkey
      and a.return_period_date = c.fdtmfilingperiod
      and c.record_effective_timestamp <= add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and (c.record_expiry_timestamp > add_months(a.date_due, 3) or
        c.record_expiry_timestamp = "9000-12-31")
  ) a1
  where a1.wanted_records = 1
),
--we need to combine START balances
tableD as
(
  select 
    nvl(d1.flngcustomerkey, d2.flngcustomerkey) flngcustomerkey,
    nvl(d1.flngaccountkey, d2.flngaccountkey) flngaccountkey,
    nvl(d1.ird_number, d2.ird_number) ird_number,
    nvl(d1.return_period_date, d2.return_period_date) return_period_date,
    nvl(d1.date_due, d2.date_due) date_due,
    nvl(d1.tax_type, d2.tax_type) tax_type,
    nvl(d1.bal_start, 0) bal_start,
    nvl(d2.bal_end, 0) bal_end

  from tableD1 d1
  full outer join tableD2 d2
  on d1.ird_number = d2.ird_number
    and d1.flngcustomerkey = d2.flngcustomerkey
    and d1.flngaccountkey = d2.flngaccountkey
    and d1.tax_type = d2.tax_type
    and d1.return_period_date = d2.return_period_date
),
--we now combine FIRST and START balances
-- we take start data if we have it
tableE as
(

  select 
    nvl(d.flngcustomerkey, c.flngcustomerkey) flngcustomerkey,
    nvl(d.flngaccountkey, c.flngaccountkey) flngaccountkey,
    nvl(d.ird_number, c.ird_number) ird_number,
    nvl(d.return_period_date, c.return_period_date) return_period_date,
    nvl(d.tax_type, c.tax_type) tax_type,
    nvl(d.date_due, c.date_due) date_due,
    nvl(d.bal_start, c.balance_start) bal_start,
    nvl(d.bal_end, c.balance_end) bal_end
  from tableC c
  full outer join tableD d
  on c.ird_number = d.ird_number
    and c.flngcustomerkey = d.flngcustomerkey
    and c.flngaccountkey = d.flngaccountkey
    and c.tax_type = d.tax_type
    and c.return_period_date = d.return_period_date
)
select *
from tableE
where bal_start <> 0 or bal_end <> 0

SELECT NDV(flngcustomerkey) AS flngcustomerkey, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(ird_number) AS ird_number, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(return_period_date) AS return_period_date, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(write_off) AS write_off, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 1, CAST(1 as DOUBLE) FROM LAB_DAUR_PROJECT.WXT_SC07FEB_3_PIT0208_SCORING_WRITEOFF_PAST

create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_writeoff_past as
--select customers that have had write off, order by date. If the latest row is a reverse, it does not count as write off
With tableA as
(
  select a1.flngcustomerkey, a1.ird_number, a1.return_period_date, a1.tax_type
  from
  (
    select a.flngcustomerkey, b.ird_number, b.return_period_date, b.tax_type,
      b.transaction_code, b.date_processed,
      row_number() over (partition by b.ird_number, b.return_period_date,
        b.tax_type order by b.date_processed desc) as rn1
    from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_dueDate_past a
    join lab_daur_project.dss_transactions b
      on a.ird_number = b.ird_number
      and a.return_period_date = b.return_period_date
      and a.tax_type = b.tax_type
      and b.date_processed between a.date_due and add_months(a.date_due, 3)
      and b.transaction_code IN ("7400", "7401", "6500", "6501") -- 7400 = HARDSHIP REMISSION, 7401 = HARDSHIP REVERSE, 6500 = CAPITALISATION
  ) a1 where a1.rn1 = 1
    and a1.transaction_code not in ("7401", "6501")
),
tableB as
(
  select a1.flngcustomerkey, a1.ird_number, a1.return_period_date, 
    case when (a1.WRITE_OFF_INC + a1.WRITE_OFF_FAM + a1.WRITE_OFF_SLS) > 0 then 1 else 0 end as WRITE_OFF
  from
  (
    select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date,
      max(case when tax_type = "INC" then 1 else 0 end) as WRITE_OFF_INC,
      max(case when tax_type = "FAM" then 1 else 0 end) as WRITE_OFF_FAM,
      max(case when tax_type = "SLS" then 1 else 0 end) as WRITE_OFF_SLS
    from tableA
    group by flngcustomerkey, ird_number, return_period_date
  ) a1
)  
select * from tableB

SELECT NDV(flngcustomerkey) AS flngcustomerkey, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(ird_number) AS ird_number, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 4, CAST(4 as DOUBLE), NDV(tax_type) AS tax_type, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), MAX(length(tax_type)), AVG(length(tax_type)), NDV(return_period_date) AS return_period_date, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(date_due) AS date_due, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(balance_start) AS balance_start, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE), NDV(balance_end) AS balance_end, CAST(-1 as BIGINT), 16, CAST(16 as DOUBLE) FROM LAB_DAUR_PROJECT.WXT_SC07FEB_3_PIT0208_SCORING_BALANCES_PAST

--get all relevant transactions for the customers in the return period
create table lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_balances_past as
With tableB1 as
(
  select a.date_due, a.flngcustomerkey, a.ird_number, b.tax_type, b.return_period_date, b.amount, b.date_processed
  from lab_daur_project.wxt_sc07Feb_3_pit0208_scoring_dueDate_past a
  join lab_daur_project.dss_transactions b
    on a.ird_number = b.ird_number
    and a.return_period_date = b.return_period_date
    and a.tax_type = b.tax_type
  where b.transaction_reason_code <> "9910"  -- 9910 is to transfer the balance to START, to essentially clear FIRST
),
-- sum up the transationcs to form the balances at specific dates, i.e. one day after due due date, 3 months after due date
tableB as
(
  select flngcustomerkey, ird_number, tax_type, return_period_date, date_due,
    sum(case when date_processed <= adddate(date_due, 1) then amount else 0 end) as balance_start,   -- due date + 1 = 08/02 or 08/04
    sum(case when date_processed <= add_months(date_due, 3) then amount else 0 end) as balance_end
  from tableB1
  group by flngcustomerkey, ird_number, tax_type, return_period_date, date_due
)
select *
from tableB

select

            record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200311
        from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200320
        where account_origin = 'START'
        and dip_account_sk > 0
        -- and account_key = '1003504896'
        and account_key = '2065829184'
        ) act
    left outer join ( --join here to get flngcustomerkey from flngaccount_key for a specific date/period (one account may belong to different customers overtime)
        select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.app_tblaccount
        from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
        -- where flngaccountkey = 1298320512 --has 2 flngcustomerkey but they're in consecutive period
        ) acct
    on cast(act.account_key as int) = acct.flngaccountkey
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between acct.record_effective_timestamp and acct.record_expiry_timestamp
    -- left outer join test_dw.app_tblprofile pp
    left outer join test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblProfile_20200320 pp
    on pp.flngcustomerkey = acct.flngcustomerkey
    and pp.fintprofilenumber = cast(act.start_parent_profile_number as int)
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between pp.record_effective_timestamp and pp.record_expiry_timestamp
    left outer join test_dw.ref_lanprofiletype ref
    on ref.fstrprofiletype = pp.fstrprofiletype

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, '' as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3,

,

group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,

select count(1) from (
	select edw.ird_number from (
		select dip_party_id, ird_number, count(*) cnt, min(record_effective_timestamp), max(record_effective_timestamp)
		from dmoa
		where party_type_code in ('IND')
		and party_origin = 'FIRST'
		group by dip_party_id, ird_number
		) ind
	full outer join (
		select dip_party_Id, ird_number, count(*) cnt, min(record_effective_timestamp), max(record_effective_timestamp)
		from dmob
		where party_type_code in ('IND')
		group by dip_party_id, ird_number
		) edw
	on ind.ird_number = edw.ird_number
	where ind.ird_number is NULL
	or edw.ird_number is NULL
	) chk_new
inner join dmoc cl
on cast(chk_new.ird_number as int) = cl.ird_number

select 
        case when start_parent_profile_type = ref.fstrdecode2 and ref.fstrdecode2 is not NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type is as expected (not N/A) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type = 'N/A' and ref.fstrdecode2 is NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type = N/A (fstrdecode is NULL) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type <> nvl(ref.fstrdecode2, 'N/A') then 'start_parent_profile_type is not as expected - CHECK!!'
             else '???' end chk,
        act.*, pp.flngcustomerkey, pp.fstrprofiletype, ref.fstrdecode2, pp.record_effective_timestamp profile_rec_eff_ts, pp.record_expiry_timestamp profile_rec_exp_ts
    from (
        select dip_account_id, account_key, account_origin, account_ird_number, account_type_code, start_profile_number, start_parent_profile_number, start_parent_profile_type, 
            record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200311
        from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200320
        where account_origin = 'START'
        and dip_account_sk > 0
        and account_key = '1003504896'
        -- and account_key = '2065829184'
        ) act
    left outer join ( --join here to get flngcustomerkey from flngaccount_key for a specific date/period (one account may belong to different customers overtime)
        select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.app_tblaccount
        from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
        -- where flngaccountkey = 1298320512 --has 2 flngcustomerkey but they're in consecutive period
        ) acct
    on cast(act.account_key as int) = acct.flngaccountkey
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between acct.record_effective_timestamp and acct.record_expiry_timestamp
    -- left outer join test_dw.app_tblprofile pp
    left outer join test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblProfile_20200320 pp
    on pp.flngcustomerkey = acct.flngcustomerkey
    and pp.fintprofilenumber = cast(act.start_parent_profile_number as int)
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between pp.record_effective_timestamp and pp.record_expiry_timestamp
    left outer join test_dw.ref_lanprofiletype ref
    on ref.fstrprofiletype = pp.fstrprofiletype

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, '' as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on 
cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = i.record_active_flag
where a.party_type = 'Individual' and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC')
or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))
and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

where flngcustomerkey = 257487616 --1200817152
order by fintprofilenumber

select 
        case when start_parent_profile_type = ref.fstrdecode2 and ref.fstrdecode2 is not NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type is as expected (not N/A) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type = 'N/A' and ref.fstrdecode2 is NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type = N/A (fstrdecode is NULL) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type <> nvl(ref.fstrdecode2, 'N/A') then 'start_parent_profile_type is not as expected - CHECK!!'
             else '???' end chk,
        act.*, pp.flngcustomerkey, pp.fstrprofiletype, ref.fstrdecode2, pp.record_effective_timestamp profile_rec_eff_ts, pp.record_expiry_timestamp profile_rec_exp_ts
    from (
        select dip_account_id, account_key, account_origin, account_ird_number, account_type_code, start_profile_number, start_parent_profile_number, start_parent_profile_type, 
            record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200311
        from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200320
        where account_origin = 'START'
        and dip_account_sk > 0
        and account_key = '1003504896'
        -- and account_key = '2065829184'
        ) act
    left outer join ( --join here to get flngcustomerkey from flngaccount_key for a specific date/period (one account may belong to different customers overtime)
        select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.app_tblaccount
        from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
        -- where flngaccountkey = 1298320512 --has 2 flngcustomerkey but they're in consecutive period
        ) acct
    on cast(act.account_key as int) = acct.flngaccountkey
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between acct.record_effective_timestamp and acct.record_expiry_timestamp
    -- left outer join test_dw.app_tblprofile pp
    left outer join test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblProfile_20200320 pp
    on pp.flngcustomerkey = acct.flngcustomerkey
    and pp.fintprofilenumber = cast(act.start_parent_profile_number as int)
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between pp.record_effective_timestamp and pp.record_expiry_timestamp
    left outer join test_dw.ref_lanprofiletype ref
    on ref.fstrprofiletype = pp.fstrprofiletype

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, '' as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on 
cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey and i.record_active_flag
where a.party_type = 'Individual' and a.record_active_flag = i.record_active_flag
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC')
or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))
and a.record_active_flag = 'Y'
group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

insert into dev_refined.rfn_account_sk_map (`dip_account_sk`,`dip_account_id`,`record_effective_timestamp`,`start_account_key`,`ird_no`,`edw_customer_type`,`edw_tax_type`,`edw_location_number`,`edw_cut_off`,`source`) select cast(ROW_NUMBER() over (order by `ird_no`,`edw_tax_type`,`edw_location_number`,`record_effective_timestamp`) + ref.etl_last_sk as bigint) as `dip_account_sk` ,`dip_account_id`,`record_effective_timestamp`,`start_account_key`,`ird_no`,`edw_customer_type`,`edw_tax_type`,`edw_location_number`,`edw_cut_off`,`source` from ( select distinct `dip_account_id` as `dip_account_id`,`record_effective_timestamp` as `record_effective_timestamp`,`start_account_key` as `start_account_key`,`ird_no` as `ird_no`,`edw_customer_type` as `edw_customer_type`,`edw_tax_type` as `edw_tax_type`,`edw_location_number` as `edw_location_number`,IF(start_account_key IS NULL, '9000-12-31', upper_cutoff) as `edw_cut_off`,`source` as `source` from dev_refined.rfn_ae_timeline l where not exists( select 1 from dev_refined.rfn_account_sk_map r where l.`record_effective_timestamp` = r.`record_effective_timestamp` and l.`ird_no` = r.`ird_no` and l.`edw_tax_type` = r.`edw_tax_type` and l.`edw_location_number` = r.`edw_location_number`) ) as main cross join ( select nvl(max(`dip_account_sk`),0) as etl_last_sk from dev_refined.rfn_account_sk_map ) as ref ;

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
-- concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, '' as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on 
cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey

where a.party_type = 'Individual' and i.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC')
or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))
and i.record_active_flag = 'Y'
group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc
select coalesce(sum(`update_object_run_key` = 15625), 0) as `count`, coalesce(count(*), 0) as `rows_written` from `dev_raw`.`app_tblnz_rtnslsobligations` where `update_object_run_key` = 15625

CREATE TABLE lab_r3_assurance_project.SE_BUSINESS_INCOME
STORED AS PARQUET AS
SELECT cast(a.ird_number as integer) as IRD_NUMBER, c.fstrfamilyname as SURNAME,  
concat(nvl(c.fstrfirstname, ''), ' ', nvl(c.fstrmiddlename, '')) as FIRST_NAMES,
c.fstrlistformataddress as ADDRESS, '' as POST_CODE, a.party_class_code as ENTITY_CLASS, nvl(a.trading_name,'') as TRADE_NAME,
a.bic_code as SIC_CODE, a.bic_desc as SIC_CODE_DESC, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_1, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_2, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_3, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc as SIC_GROUPING_LEVEL_4
,
min(i.fstrincometype) as MIN_TYPE
from prod_refined_restricted_access.party_dim a
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblcustomerinfo c on cast(a.customer_key as integer) = c.flngcustomerkey and a.record_active_flag = c.record_active_flag
join prod_raw_restricted_access.app_tblnz_income i on 
cast(a.customer_key as integer) = i.flngcustomerkey

where a.party_type = 'Individual' and i.record_active_flag = 'Y'
and i.fdtmdate >= '2019-03-31 00:00:00'
and (i.fstrincometype in ('BUSINC','EXPNSE','OTHINC','PTRINC','SLFINC','OTHINC')
or (i.fstrincometype in ('SHREMP','LTCINC','WT') and i.fcuramount <> 0))
and i.record_active_flag = 'Y'
group by a.ird_number, c.fstrfamilyname,  
c.fstrfirstname, c.fstrmiddlename,
c.fstrlistformataddress, a.party_class_code, a.trading_name,
a.bic_code, a.bic_desc, 
a.anzsic_level1_desc, 
a.anzsic_level2_desc, 
a.anzsic_level3_desc, 
a.anzsic_level4_desc

select count(distinct from_ird_number,from_ceased, flngfromcustomerkey, fstrlinktype, relationship_active, distance, flngtocustomerkey, to_ird_number, to_ceased, order_rank, flnglinkkey, fblnactive, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease) as nbr
from tmp_assoc_ent_all

select 
        case when start_parent_profile_type = ref.fstrdecode2 and ref.fstrdecode2 is not NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type is as expected (not N/A) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type = 'N/A' and ref.fstrdecode2 is NULL then 'start_parent_profile_type = N/A (fstrdecode is NULL) - OK'
             when start_parent_profile_type <> nvl(ref.fstrdecode2, 'N/A') then 'start_parent_profile_type is not as expected - CHECK!!'
             else '???' end chk,
        act.*, pp.flngcustomerkey, pp.fstrprofiletype, pp.record_effective_timestamp profile_rec_eff_ts, pp.record_expiry_timestamp profile_rec_exp_ts, ref.fstrdecode2
    from (
        select dip_account_id, account_key, account_origin, account_ird_number, account_type_code, start_profile_number, start_parent_profile_number, start_parent_profile_type, 
            record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200311
        from test_dw.md_backup_refined_account_dim_20200320
        where account_origin = 'START'
        and dip_account_sk > 0
        and account_key = '1003504896'
        -- and account_key = '2065829184'
        ) act
    left outer join ( --join here to get flngcustomerkey from flngaccount_key for a specific date/period (one account may belong to different customers overtime)
        select flngaccountkey, flngcustomerkey, fdtmcommence, fdtmcease, record_effective_timestamp, record_expiry_timestamp 
        -- from test_dw.app_tblaccount
        from test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblAccount_20200320
        -- where flngaccountkey = 1298320512 --has 2 flngcustomerkey but they're in consecutive period
        ) acct
    on cast(act.account_key as int) = acct.flngaccountkey
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between acct.record_effective_timestamp and acct.record_expiry_timestamp
    -- left outer join test_dw.app_tblprofile pp
    left outer join test_dw.md_backup_raw_app_tblProfile_20200320 pp
    on pp.flngcustomerkey = acct.flngcustomerkey
    and pp.fintprofilenumber = cast(act.start_parent_profile_number as int)
    and act.record_expiry_timestamp between pp.record_effective_timestamp and pp.record_expiry_timestamp
    left outer join test_dw.ref_lanprofiletype ref
    on ref.fstrprofiletype = pp.fstrprofiletype
